    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="488"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Presidents Special Assistant</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HHL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the British Secretary of State for Foreign
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eden</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">and Reply</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d488fn1">This exchange of handwritten notes presumably
                        occurred during the quadripartite dinner meeting of December 5, 1943, <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_733">p. 733</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-05">December 5 (?),
                            1943</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_EA1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Anthony</hi>
                    </persName> Has he<note n="2" xml:id="d488fn2">Presumably <persName
                            corresp="#p_II1">Inönü</persName>.</note> been told squadrons do not go
                    in until Feb 15? Is there good reason not to tell him</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Yes; he has been told. <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Winston</persName> gave
                        him a paper this afternoon.<note n="3" xml:id="d488fn3">The paper under
                            reference was presumably the “plan” mentioned in the tripartite meeting
                            that afternoon; see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_714"
                                >p. 714</ref>.</note> He understands, but issue is he won’t agree to
                        flying in until his <hi rend="italic">army</hi> is ready. This looks like a
                        long job.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
